<a name="5436"></a>

<div class="sub-content-header">Mark Your Calendars – 2011 Exhibitor Workshop is Here!</div>
<br />


        <p style="margin-right: 0px;" dir="ltr"><img alt="" style="float: right;"  src="/images/photos/laptop.jpg" />Once again, CES is presenting exhibitors with the CES Exhibitor Workshop webcast series. This free, four-part webcast series starts in September and provides exhibitors with the CliffsNotes-style information you need to succeed at CES. From marketing and PR tips and logistics information to our vendors GES and Map Your Show, the series covers it all.<br />
        <br />
        Also, if you register for the workshop, you’ll receive access to the CES official vendor discount codes to receive discounts from some of our official CES vendors. <br />
        <br />
        <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/workshop/rd_registration2012.asp">Registration is now open</a>.<br />
        <br />
        <strong>Using MyCES to Maximize Your ROI <br />
        </strong>2 p.m. EST Thursday, September 15, 2011 <br />
        <br />
        Join us for a free webcast and learn how to leverage your opportunities on the online exhibitor directory and floor plan before, during AND after the show. <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/workshop/rd_registration2012.asp">Register now</a>! <br />
        <br />
        <strong>Optimize Your Marketing Resources and Get the Most Press Coverage</strong> <br />
        2 p.m. EST Thursday, September 22, 2011 <br />
        <br />
        The CES Marketing and Communications teams provide you with free tools to market your booth and get the press coverage you need for a successful show. <a  target="_blank" href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/workshop/rd_registration2012.asp">Register now</a>!<br />
        <br />
        <strong>Meet GES – Official Show Contractor <br />
        </strong>2 p.m. EST Tuesday, October 11, 2011<br />
        <br />
        A panel of GES experts discuss shipping deadlines and rigging, booth design and maintenance, electrical issues, union jurisdictions and material handling, and anything else you need to know to ensure your materials reach the show efficiently. <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/workshop/rd_registration2012.asp">Register now</a>! <br />
        <br />
        <strong>CES Operations – Show Planning and Booth Logistics <br />
        </strong>2 p.m. Wednesday October 19, 2011 – 2 p.m. EST <br />
        <br />
        The CES Operations team helps make your booth planning easier with tips on navigating the show, securing hotel reservation, ordering booth services and setting up your booth within show guidelines. <a  href="http://www.cesweb.org/exhibitors/resources/workshop/rd_registration2012.asp">Register now</a>!</p>
    <br />
